e string alternating\n        if abs(count_0 - count_1) > 1:\n            return -1\n        \n        # Helper function to calculate the number of swaps needed to match the pattern\n        def calculate_swaps(pattern):\n            swaps = 0\n            for i in range(len(s)):\n                if s[i] != pattern[i]:\n                    swaps += 1\n            return swaps // 2  # Each swap fixes two positions\n        \n        # Determine the possible alternating patterns\n        if count_0 > count_1:\n            # Pattern starts with '0'\n            pattern = '01' * (len(s) // 2) + '0'\n        elif count_1 > count_0:\n            # Pattern starts with '1'\n            pattern = '10' * (len(s) // 2) + '1'\n        else:\n            # Two possible patterns: starting with '0' or '1'\n            pattern1 = '01' * (len(s) // 2)\n            pattern2 = '10' * (len(s) // 2)\n            return min(calculate_swaps(pattern1), calculate_swaps(pattern2))\n        \n        # Calculate and return the number of swaps needed for the determined pattern\n        return calculate_swaps(pattern)\n```\n\nThis solution first checks if it's possible to make the string alternating by comparing the counts of '0's and '1's. If the difference is more than 1, it returns -1. Otherwise, it calculates the minimum number of swaps needed to match one of the possible alternating patterns. If the counts of '0's and '1's are equal, it considers both possible starting patterns ('0101...' and '1010...') and returns the minimum number of swaps needed for either pattern.", "estimated_date": 1621123200000}